                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.4016/287a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Philip</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-16T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 16, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2758. Reports have reached the Department that situation of Armenian exiles in
                    Mesopotamia is daily becoming worse—that great numbers are dying of hunger and
                    sickness, and children are sold openly in markets. If true, again urge Turkish
                    Government in name of humanity to alleviate condition remnants of this race.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
